         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/4/85.  ¶  ¶ Our autumn here, dear Sir Joseph, is the best time for lifting Xanthorrhoeas; so I have procured 2 about 120 miles from Melbourne  ¶ and  ¶ send them now quite fresh by the "Garrone" pa...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">85.04.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1882-90, f. 143.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/4/85. <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">MS annotations</seg> And June 22/85' <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[letter not found] and</seg> Two stems of <name key="Xanthorrhoea%20australis">Xanthorrhoea australis</name> arrd at Kew ex S.S. "Garonne" June 20th 1885. They are apparently in perfectly healthy condition W.W. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">[presumably William Watson, assistant curator from 1885].</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Our autumn here, dear Sir Joseph, is the best time for lifting Xanthorrhoeas; so I have procured 2 about 120 miles from Melbourne <seg style="color: #000000; ">and </seg>send them now quite fresh by the "Garrone" packed in a strong close case; Mr Dyer having expressed a wish to be supplied for Kew with any of the species.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">Letter not found but see</seg> M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 25 January 1885 (in this edition as 85-01-25a).</p>
               </note> The one, now sent, is the true X. australis.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">X. australis needs heathy-moory sand-soil, which from time to time should be renewed otherwise the plant simply dies from exhaustion.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Xanthorrhoea%20australis">Xanthorrhoea australis</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
